FAQ: Domain name

What’s a domain name?

A domain name is what someone types into a browser to find a website - it’s like your online home address. For instance, in the web address www.wix.com, the full domain name is 'wix.com' and “.com” is the domain extension. When you register a custom website domain name, it can help you get found easier, boost your online presence, look more professional and help you to build trust with your audience.

Visit our blog for tips on choosing a domain name and for help choosing a business name, check out our business name generator. Together, these two tools can enhance your online presence.

Why do I need a domain name?

Your domain name is your online identity, the key to standing out and looking professional on the web. It's what helps people find and remember you in the vast digital landscape. Whether you're a big brand or a one-man show, having a unique and memorable website domain name is essential for making a lasting impact for your online presence.

What domain extensions can I use with a free domain name?

Your free domain voucher is valid for a wide variety of domain name extensions, including: .com, .net, .org and many more. Here you can find the complete list of available domain extensions that you can register with Wix.


As you choose the right extension for your domain name, consider the audience you’re targeting, as well as the type of website you’re creating. Most common top-level domains are .com and .net, however, a more specific extension, such as .shop, .site or .studio, can help you create the domain name you want, as well as make your site address easier to remember.

How can I get a free domain name?

When you choose an annual Wix website plan, you'll receive a voucher for a free domain name of your choice for one year. You can pick from a variety of options from our TLD list including .com, .net, .store and country-specific codes. Redeem your voucher within two months to claim your domain.

How can I connect or transfer my domain name?

Connecting your Wix website domain to an external site on the internet? Simply follow the steps in our support article. If you purchased a domain name from Wix and want to connect it to your Wix site, find easy-to-follow instructions here. Need to transfer your Wix domains to a different Wix account? See how in this guide, we're here to assist you at every step.

Is my personal information protected at Wix?

At Wix, we take privacy and security seriously. That's why we offer domain privacy protection when you purchase and register domains with us. By choosing Wix as your registrar, your personal contact details in the public WHOIS database will be replaced with Wix’s contact information. This helps prevent unwanted solicitors and spammers from accessing your personal information. For more about how domain name privacy protection works at Wix, check out this article.

Do I need to renew my domain registration or is it automatic?

When you buy domains from Wix, they are set to automatically renew 30 days before their expiration date. To learn how to check your domain renewal date, check out this article on extending your domain registration. You can also add up to 3 additional years to your domain registration by extending your subscription with auto renewal.

How do I permanently buy a domain name?

Once you’ve chosen your domain name and provided your registration information, you can go on to the next step; domain purchase. To buy a domain with Wix, simply select a time-frame (from 1 to 3 years) and complete the payment process. Wix takes care of submitting all of your domain name registration details, so you can go ahead and create your website and then start using your officially registered domain name right away.

Can I get lifetime ownership of a domain?

When you purchase a domain name with Wix, it can be bought for 1-3 years. Once that time is up, you can renew it and continue to renew it as long as you want.

What should I know before buying a domain name?

Before you purchase a domain name, choose one that's relevant, easy to remember and simple to spell. Pick the right extension (.com, .net, .org) based on your business and audience. Use important keywords to boost search visibility and keep it short to avoid confusion. Keep in mind when browsing for a domain provider that you should keep an eye out for extra fees for things like privacy protection. Also be on the lookout for other extras like hosting, ICANN and DNS services—with Wix these come included with all domains.
